# Files in this repo that NexusMind owns and that the deploy scripts must
# refuse to sync.
#
# This is a controlled-divergence escape hatch — entries should always have a
# tracked issue and a resolution deadline. Empty is the steady state. Long-term
# silent divergence is the bug-shape that the 2026-05-04 "manifest as
# anti-pattern" entry in memory/gotcha-log.md warns against: it lets
# production-only code drift undetected from upstream, and the very mechanism
# meant to protect that code hides regressions when the divergence stops being
# actively maintained (concrete: normalization plumbing was deleted from
# NexusMind on 2026-04-16 and went unnoticed for 18 days).
#
# Production-runtime concerns now live in NexusMind/src/scoring/production_scorer.py
# (a wrapper that composes the shared base scorer). filter_base_scorer.py and
# hybrid_scorer.py are pure shared math, synced freely. See ADR-014.
#
# scripts/deploy_to_nexusmind.{sh,ps1} read this manifest and refuse to copy
# any listed files into the NexusMind checkout. The mechanism stays in place
# for genuine short-lived divergence (e.g. a back-port window during a
# refactor) — add an entry with a tracked issue, resolve it, remove the entry.
#
# Format: one path per line, relative to the llm-distillery repo root. Forward
# slashes. `#` starts a comment; blank lines ignored. The deploy scripts will
# refuse to start if a listed path doesn't exist on either side (typo guard).
#
# Cross-reference: NexusMind/memory/patterns.md "Filter Sync" section. Update
# both when adding/removing entries.

